This is an aim map designed to be headshot only. Use it to practice against bots (videos: http://tinyurl.com/y9d57gd http://tinyurl.com/ya28mg5 ) or with your friends or in a random pub. You cannot rush the tunnels are too long you would die, but you can get to the other spawn to kill afks/campers You spawn with an AK, deagle, vesthelm for the fairness, but you can also buy whatever you want. Bots run a course kind of like a tower defense so it's really good to use this to practice against bots. Please click here for more information http://y3sak.crazedhosting.com/wb/pages/aim_tex_headshot-tower-d-explanation.php it's my website. This map has many different buildings, all of which you can enter and shoot from the windows,the roofs or the balconies.
However, what makes this map special is the underground tunnels, which are connected to the surface through many different points by ladders or even underwater tunnels. This special feature makes the map much more exciting as fighting can take place in two different areas and you can use the tunnels to travel from one place to another.

The map includes a very simple 3D skybox which makes the map look much larger. I have thought about adding bombsites, but I don't know where. Do you think the map is fine as it is, or should I add bomsites? Please comment.

My first fully completed map, used by my clan for warmups and muck arounds.

The map is split into two halves by a huge wall, with various ways through, around and over it.

I've tried to make this map as varied as possible, allowing a wide range of weapons and tactics.  There are a few sniper spots dotted around the map, along with narrow corridors for SMGs.  Both spawns are fairly well protected, but neither offers any attacking options for potential campers, so it should keep the map lively and flowing.

I've included a few "secret areas" that involve timed jumping rather than fake walls, and these secrets are balanced out by the fact you are exposed whilst trying to get to them.

I hope you enjoy, and I should have more to come soon :)

(ps: this is my first AND ONLY texture map)
